annotation.TEXT: I wonder why there are hidden blocks here, when I can just use the Hammer Bro. platform... Maybe just in case that platform fails to spawn.
So, I guess that piece of a midway gate is just a physics-defying force field that keeps the water in, but lets me go through it.
BGM: Touhou 6 - Cirno's Theme - Beloved Tomboyish Daughter
Yeah, there's the shell he was supposed to have. Maybe it despawned for some reason.

...This! It's Ketchup Adventure by mockingod! This wasn't requested by anyone, but I wanted to give Touhou Mario a break until next week, because of... reasons. In the meantime, I've randomly picked a short hack from SMW Central to play.
But, what if I don't wanna abandon ye hope?
BGM: Final Fantasy 6 - The Decisive Battle
Whoa, it's gotten bigger!
I don't know. Boat? Helicopter? Warp whistle? A wizard did it?

Man, this seems like it should be urgent, but I'm just waiting around for the autoscroll to bring new stuff into play. Also, notice how I'm not automatically scrolling down with the vines that I'm holding onto.
Oh, man. Look at all that ketchup oozing from those pipes... At least I hope it's ketchup, and not lava. Okay, let's get this party started, since nothing else happens on the title screen.
I didn't like the sound of that... "Oh, crap" indeed! A wall of searing hot ketchup is advancing on me, and I'm pretty sure that would not be good for my health, even if it is tasty!
So, yeah. Now how am I supposed to beat Bowser? Well, since he's acting like the classic SMB1 Bowser, maybe I can still burn him to death.
Whoa, that was a lucky stomp! I did not see that shell coming!
There we go. Now, it gets faster with each hit, of course, which makes it trickier to hit it with Bob-omb explosions.
And now I'm ready to turn up the heat as well!
Alright, that was the last Yoshi coin, so that puts my mind at ease regarding those. But, where do I go now?
Heh. My fireballs are going through the slope over here. Fireballs don't exactly detect ceiling slopes well...
Huh. No number of players choice?

Alright, Tap-Taps can be shell-killed. And yeah, that's what happens when one of these Tap-Tap sprites dies-- It just floats there for some reason. But, it is actually dead. If I scroll the dead sprite off screen and then come back, it won't respawn.
Deus ex machina!
BGM: CUSTOM - Volcanisimo by spigmike
Hello, and welcome to... a thunder sound effect! And, also...
Wheeeeee!!!
BGM: Cave Story - Living Waterway
Oh, well. Forget those few coins that I can no longer reach.
Ha! See, I'm perfectly capable of frying fish that are near the ceiling without screwing up!

Okay, let's do this right this time. Use the brief moment of invincibility that the game mysteriously gives me to pass harmlessly through Bowser and his attacks, then stomp the P-switch without ever picking it up!
What?! You had I don't know how many opportunities to get some ketchup and you didn't get any?!
Barf! I screwed up my timing there.
Oh, man. This one starts stunning me after I've hit it twice. That definitely makes things trickier!
Yeah, yeah. I get it. Time up. Well, how much progress did I lose? Wait, I never did hit a midpoint, did I?
Part of a midway gate? Weird. But, I saw stuff up here that I want to check out.
Let's go to double ludicrous speed (x16) for this...
Glitched demo count: 2
BGM: Cave Story - Running Hell
Nuts, the springboard's locked in its current position (probably so the player can't trap himself here), so I don't think I'll be able to backtrack and get every single coin up there...
I definitely pressed my luck there, but fortunately, I avoided the Whammy and landed on a trip to Cancun. How nice!
Oh, this is a good time to see if I can slide-kill a Tap-Tap. If I get hurt, there's a replacement flower right there.
Pfft, of course. I didn't have to shell jump at all. Why didn't I think to check for a hidden block sooner?
Well, then they must not've studied hard enough.

Yeah, nuts to this. Since I died as a result of an unexpected glitch that occurred by accident, I'm going to do a space-time rewind instead of redoing about 7 or 8 minutes of stuff. I hope this is okay with everyone.
Whoa! I wasn't expecting that! Wow, so I guess the heart of the volcano is a literal heart!
Sure, let's have one last multi-coin block before I enter that important-looking double-door.
Oh, maybe I'm not meant to enter it.
Alright, it's boss time, against... What the heck is that? It looks like an actual... heart?
Gold? I want gold. But, I guess I should head towards that chilly-looking area instead.
Wow, there was actually a multi-coin block there? Also, forget that power up.
Alright, nailed it first try. Hmm... But, I wonder how you're normally supposed to get up here?
Glitched demo count: 1 (The glitch was when I kicked the P-switch through the wall.)
Yeah, I'm good.
Alright, they're slide-killable!

That unlocks nothing new, and I can't move anywhere new, so yeah, I guess I'm done! I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Ketchup Adventure 1! That "1" makes me wonder if there'll be a sequel...
Oh, man. Berries. Could there be a Yoshi nearby?

Aww... I just thought of this. This would've been the perfect place to put in Flame Hyenard's actual voiced lines! Oh, well. BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! WOO! TRI-FORMATION! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN TO THE GROUND!
Oh, my god. That is so silly. We've got to see some replays of that...
Oh, what?! I certainly wasn't expecting that!
And here's our overworld. Oh, man. Look at all that ketchup (I'm assuming it's ketchup). Also, listen to that music.

Whoa. Well, that shell just landed in the molten ketchup. Also, I never would've figured out the name of this "Volcanisimo" song if it weren't for that helpful song list in the included "Credits.txt" file!
They can be Goomba-killed as well. That's nice.
Now, let's watch this Spike Top casually walk into the hot sauce here...
Turbo A for no reason! Also, spin jump sound effects, just because!
Space-time rewind count: 2
There! Easy enough, if you don't glitch the P-switch out of bounds by accident! But, did I miss a Yoshi coin somewhere? Or is the level not quite done yet?
Hmm... Now how do I get up there? Maybe with a shell jump?
Did I ever hit a midpoint? No, of course I didn't. So, once again, nuts to this! I'm going back in time!
Oh, wow. Really? I thought I was giving Touhou Mario a break! But this hack suddenly has the strongest theme of all in it!
Space-time rewind count: 1
Whoops. I was going to shell-kill all of them, but I fried the shell by accident. Oh, well.
Yep, the lava was made of teleport blocks!
Okay, so now let's not get anywhere near any ceilings of any kind while climbing any of these vines! Any questions?
Well, I didn't see that anti-stunlock move coming! Oh, but what's happening now... Did I... win?
But you're still hungry... Oh, wait. That's a different game.
Yeah, I just sorta casually-like accidentally picked up the P-switch and kicked it through the wall.
Okay, that's enough looking at the ketchup ocean, and while I'd like to sit here and listen to this music, I really should start playing the game now.
...Really? Did I seriously just do that?
I'd better be careful when hitting this multi-coin block.
Geez, how long is this level?! And I still haven't seen a midpoint yet! Is that ketchup-colored water safe? I'll do a "science" on it...
Oh, but that's it. No other additional tricks I guess.
I hope that shell will respawn, though I don't see why it wouldn't.
Waaaiiit a minute...
Alright, so I'm restarting from the beginning of this room, and I'm not going to get glitch-killed anymore... I hope!
That shell-less koopa tried to ambush me but just missed. Ha.
Oh, man. I gotta trust Bowser? Well, to be honest. I can't really do anything else. I can't even time out suicide, since the timer's set to zero, so entering the lava is my only option.
Sucks for Chuck.
Aww... No custom P-switch music? Oh, well.
Oh, man. So, we're going to be competing with Bowser I take it, and that's why we're going to beat up Bowser during this quest.
Yeah, it's perfectly safe, and there are hidden blocks so that I can get out.
Well, I guess I'll let this Wind Fortress theme play out for about a minute and a half more so you guys can listen to it some more if you want. See you all later!
Oh, I guess the level's not over yet. There's some Tap-Tap the Tap-Taps that I gotta get past.
And, it's boss time! Ooh, thanks for the brief invincibility!
Alright, I'm done cleaning that place out. Let's move on.

Huh. I expected those purple blocks to be burnable or grabbable. But instead, I can pass right through them into this treasure trove cove. And then while I'm there, I can go into a sandcastle and input so many cheat codes that my save file gets erased. Oh, wait. That's a different game.
Okay, maybe the cold is affecting his motor skills... And by that, I mean I screwed up the fireball timing on that fish.
Oh, man! I guess I should get out of here before I become a tasty french fry!
Huh. I wonder if the second blue koopa was also supposed to be kicking a shell there...
I wonder how icy cold this water is? Well, it can't be too cold, because Mario can swim in it just fine.
Geez, what's a multi-coin block doing here?
Nuts. I must've hit him with several dozen shots, but he just would not die. Darn, why wasn't this custom Bowser sprite coded to die to fireballs?
BGM: Romancing Saga 3 - Last Battle
Well, of course I killed them. It's what I do.
Alright, that's my fourth Yoshi coin, so why is this video only about one-third done? Maybe the Yoshi coin placement is a bit lopsided in this level, and I get them all before midpoint or something.
Alright, a pipe, but how do I enter it?
Oh, I think I can stunlock this thing and just keep comboing it! LOL!
Man, a lot of this is me just waiting around for the next platform I have to hop on to appear. This is more boring than urgent.
Well, it doesn't take a rocket scientist to figure this one out. It takes a brain surgeon instead.
Heh. The floating terrain there looks like a grinning face with a goatee, or something.
Uh, oh. This passage is turning red over here.
And, as expected, there's the silver P-switch.
Not quite enough height, but maybe if I do it from the pipe on the left...
Oh, man. So I had to go to the very core of the Ketchup Volcano to get my ketchup?
C-C-C-C-COMBO BREAKER!!!
Yep, it's another reset door.
I guess Blarggs love boiling hot ketchup! Which I guess would make sense.
I had a feeling this one had multiple coins too for some reason.
Uh, oh. Peach is forcing Mario to do... something! Also, we may as well beat up Bowser for the heck of it, too!
BGM: Chrono Trigger - Wind Scene
BGM: Super Mario Bros. Metal Version by worldpeace
BGM: Cave Story - Wind Fortress
Oh, man. Flashback (I assume). Also, you have to press "X" to advance these dialogues. "Y" won't do it.
Oh, it's just the Thwomp boss. This should be a piece of cake, unless this is one of those Thwomp bosses that have some additional surprises...

And that's it. I wonder why there was no midpoint in such a long level, and I wonder why the game gave me brief invincibility after some screen transitions. That invincibility made the Bowser fight trivial (if you don't count the P-swtich through the wall glitch).
Okay, finally. I'm surprised I didn't accidentally burn the shell in the process. However, there was nothing of interest up there. Why tease me with that ledge then?!
Alright, so our adventure begins with us powering up, climbing a vine, and grabbing the first Yoshi coin.
Well, there was an obvious hidden 1-up. Now, if I shell jump up there, will I find anything?
Just seeing if the P-switch made anything else appear over here. Also, that Tap-Tap I shell-killed a moment ago is completely gone now.
Gee, I wonder if I'll need a silver P-switch to get in there.
Okay, maybe I'm meant to enter this pipe!
DOUBLE KILL!
BGM: Kirby and the Amazing Mirror - Radish Ruins
I guess that's a reset door, which means there must be a messupable (is that even a word?) puzzle around here.
Yay, mushroom that I don't need.
What is with me and hitting nasty/silly glitches in this hack?
I missed with that one...

Now, this hack came with a "Credits.txt" file, and it includes a list of all of the songs used in this hack, so I should easily be able to identify any songs that would've otherwise stumped me (such as this Wind Fortress theme).
Change these periods into question marks. (Geez, even if I'm not playing Touhou Mario, I'm finding typos in a hack.)
There sure are a lot of multi-coin blocks around here...
I'm carefully avoiding that vine/ceiling glitch here.

Gee, I wonder where I should go from here? Should I jump around cluelessly for a couple minutes while Yakety Sax plays? Or should I recognize right away that these indents in the dirt walls are climbable? I'll choose the latter this time.

Oh, this was one of those shells that actually acts like a parakoopa in a way. If a shell-less koopa enters it, it becomes a bouncing parakoopa, and if it's kicked, it takes 2 stomps to stop it (the first stomp removing the "parakoopa" property from it).
